Some either actual schizophrenic or a LARPer keeps spamming threads on /x/ about concrete containing blood and all cities being "paved with blood", but that's something Cormac McCarthy also mentioned in "The Stonemason", Mesoamerican concrete being made with mixed-in human blood.

There is a patent you can find just by googling it, but I think Roman concrete supposedly being self-healing and repairing its cracks passively with time is related to containing blood. Per McCarthy it's also why masons use free stones and lime mortar, keep the craft bloodless.

Finally, but the entire thing reminds me of an obscure Ray Peat article (email?) about how regular dough behaves differently depending on if you mix various substances into the flour. Like dough with stimulants in it feels different that regular dough in your hands. Very bizarre.

Dr. Rudolf Steiner said Nietzsche (whom he met) fought the Antichrist in combat and almost defeated him, but lost and had his mind destroyed in the process. One wonders how many men today fight the powers of the night in their sleep and bear brutal invisible scars on their souls.

Chesterton IIRC also had one weird passage where he alluded to wrestling with an angel one midnight. I think it all ties in with the Balkan concept of some somnambulic men leaving their bodies at night and fighting wind weather-demons, one Montengrin Orthodox saint was like that.

I recall one more contemporary figure who opposed what was meant to be the incarnation of the Antichrist and became schizophrenic in the process, I guess it's like the electric current metaphor that Evola enjoyed, it just fries your brain in a very direct, physics-like way.
